<TEXT>
the flood of soviet immigrants into israel 
has roused fears among arabs that the jewish state will shun peace 
efforts and seek more land for a rapidly growing population 
they also worry about the improved eastwest relations that made 
the increased flow possible and about the political revolution in 
eastern europe 
i dont think weve faced a more serious matter since the 
1930s when a massive jewish immigration to palestine took place 
foreign minister marwan kassem of jordan told the weekly star 
newspaper last month 
at least 300000 soviet jews are expected to reach israel in the 
next few years because of the kremlins relaxed emigration rules 
they now arrive at the rate of about 1200 a week 
that will alter the palestinian demographic equation that 
because of a higher birth rate they eventually would outnumber 
jews in israel as well as the occupied west bank and gaza strip 
the emigration issue is only one consequence of the new detente 
which many arabs believe seriously undermines their strategy 
against israel 
such longtime radical allies of moscow as syria and libya 
already feel the cooling in moscow caused by political 
liberalization and are edging back to the arab mainstream 
in what used to be the soviet bloc democratic governments are 
replacing the rigid communist regimes that backed the arabs some 
of the new governments have renewed relations with israel which 
their predecessors broke in 1967 
these developments have spurred efforts to forge a new arab 
unity there is talk of reviving a military alliance of iraq syria 
and jordan on israels borders 
kassem compared the mass soviet emigration to 1948 when israel 
was born and hundreds of thousands of palestinians fled to jordan 
syria lebanon and egypt 
yasser arafat chairman of the palestine liberation 
organization and secretarygeneral chedli klibi of the arab league 
called the immigration a catastrophe kuwaits cabinet said it 
was flagrant aggression 
about 1 million jews have applied to leave the soviet union and 
israeli officials say they expect about 300000 to arrive in the 
next three years israels jewish population now is about 4 million 
in a statement to israel radio last month prime minister 
yitzhak shamir said arabs oppose all immigration for them 
the immigration of soviet jews to israel is a sign of defeat in 
their war against the state of israel and zionism 
arabs see the mass influx as creating a stronger israel less 
willing to make peace on terms arabs consider acceptable 
israel already stands as the major military power in the area 
so any increase is bound to worry us said kamel abu jaber a 
political scientist at the university of jordan 
we know there are something like 3 million soviet jews were 
talking about the first stage of 1 million arriving when will the 
other 2 million arrive where will be the next jump 
he and other arab analysts believe the latest wave of 
immigration also could 
bring new jewish settlers to the west bank gaza strip and 
golan heights all of which israel captured in 1967 the return of 
those lands is a key element in all arab peace plans and most 
others 
this influx will make israel more instransigent in denying 
palestinian rights to regain their lands the united arab 
emirates said 
increase israeli pressure on palestinians in the occupied 
lands to move to jordan which could threaten the stability of a 
nation bordering the two most important oil states saudi arabia 
and iraq 
king hussein of jordan said that fits what he described as plans 
of israeli hardliners to make jordan a substitute palestinian 
state 
deal another blow to the hope millions of palestinians have of 
returning to their homeland or creating a palestinian state in the 
west bank and gaza 
our own refugees who have spent most of their lives scattered 
around the world without a home have the priority over soviet jews 
to return to their homeland palestine said a petition signed by 
85 members of the palestine national council which acts as the plo 
legislature 
revive an old fear that zionists will achieve their dream of 
gathering most jews into palestine creating pressure for expansion 
into areas of lebanon and jordan that israeli religious extremists 
consider part of the ancient land of israel 
israel has declared its expansionist nature and has proved 
that nature said abu jaber the jordanian political scientist 
</TEXT>
