uproar that began three days earlier when president bush said aid 
to israel could be affected by the israeli governments policy of 
settling jews on captured land 
that land includes east jerusalem 
for 23 years israel and the united states have disagreed about 
the status of jerusalem a city fought over for centuries because 
it is holy to jews christians and moslems 
although the united states and most other countries have never 
recognized israels annexation of east jerusalem us presidents 
have previously not challenged israels building programs there 
the council resolution repeats israels stand that jerusalems 
arab eastern sector annexed after its capture from jordan along 
with the west bank in the 1967 middle east war was part of the 
eternal capital of the jewish people 
