administration would 
limit to 250000 the amount fmha could write down for any one 
borrower 
allow a borrower only one writedown and one net recovery buyout 
let the fmha consider all of the borrowers assets except 
those necessary for family living when calculating a writedown 
currently the agency only considers the assets used in calculating 
the original loan 
extend from two years to 10 years the time that the government 
has to collect profits made by farmers who sell their property 
after buying out their loan at net recovery value 
require borrowers to act in good faith as defined by fmha 
regulations to be eligible for net recovery buyouts 
extend the time periods in which borrowers may apply for 
restructuring in which fmha must process these applications and in 
which borrowers may exercise the option for a net recovery buyout 
