hekmaytar 
hekmatyar a 42yearold engineer has broken with the 
guerrillas exile gpvernment formed a year ago in neighboring 
pakistan and has been accused by other resistance groups of killing 
rival guerrillas and innocent civilians 
he is among the most antiwest leaders of the seven insurgent 
groups but has received the bulk of us weapons during the 
12yearold civil war in afghanistan 
tanai a leader of the coup that installed a marxist government 
in april 1968 is said to have had many contacts with the moslem 
guerrillas 
reports circulated in july that tanai and hekmatyar were 
conspiring to overthrow najib the alleged coup plot was uncovered 
and tanai was either detained or put under house arrest briefly 
according to later reports 
the general believed to be in his 40s has opposed najibs 
peace overtures najib has made various offers to the guerrillas in 
an attempt to end the civil war but to no avail 
in december the government arrested 127 people who allegedly 
were planning a coup tanai was implicated but never charged and 
was said to have spent weeks under house arrest 
on monday 124 of those arrested went on trial in kabul 
including senior army officers the other three were released 
hekmatyar told reporters tuesday in islamabad he supports any 
attempt to oust najib if a coup succeeded he said the guerrillas 
would decide whether to negotiate for an islamic government or 
fight najibs successor 
soviet foreign ministry spokesman gennady i gerasimov was asked 
in moscow tuesday what action the kremlin would take if najib was 
overthrown he replied we will just have to wait and see 
the red army entered afghanistan in december 1979 to help fight 
the war the last soviet forces withdrew on feb 15 1989 but the 
kremlin continues to provide massive aid 
</TEXT>
