sen alfonse damato under scrutiny by the 
senate ethics committee is asking federal agencies to send him 
copies of any documents concerning him that have been released 
under the freedom of information act 
the request which an official at one department said could 
result in a paperwork nightmare if granted was made last month 
in a series of letters the new york republicans office sent to the 
14 cabinet departments and several other agencies 
damatos press secretary franklin l coleman who signed the 
letters said the intense local media scrutiny damato has received 
in recent months has often included questions about correspondence 
no longer quickly available to the senator because it has been sent 
to archives 
we made this request in order to be in a position to respond 
promptly and accurately to inquiries regarding correspondence our 
office generated to agencies in the past coleman said tuesday 
the letters on senate stationery said damatos office has 
received inquiries about correspondence and indications that 
similar requests for the documents had been filed with government 
agencies under the freedom of information act 
