meet the requirements of the freedom of information act because it 
does not ask for a specific document or documents 
although colemans letter was not filed as an foia request 
eiland said the commission had decided to treat it as such 
eiland also said it was office policy to treat confidentially 
any media requests for research assistance we never ever tell 
another person what someone else is looking at he said its 
between us and the reporter 
