despite investors expectations he said 
market players have expected the central bank would raise its 
official discount rate after general elections last month and 
analysts have blamed the markets recent decline in part on 
uncertainties over the key interest rate 
the discount rate hike has gradually been factored into the 
market but the problem is its timing inoue said 
this is a triplelow situation with declines in all the 
markets stock foreign exchange and bonds said masayoshi yano 
a dealer with nikko securities co 
he said a frontpage story today in the financial newspaper 
nihon keizai shimbun saying the bank of japan would raise its 
official discount rate from the current 425 percent by as much as 
1 percentage point as early as next week discouraged stock 
investors 
inoue said the index which fell even farther in the morning 
remained low as individual investors continued to sell issues while 
very few participants were buying 
dealers attributed the indexs early decline to programaided 
arbitrage selling initiated by foreign securities firms such as 
morgan stanley salomon brothers and shearson lehman 
the last day for futures issues due in march is scheduled for 
tomorrow so i expect continuing arbitrage selling until the end of 
tomorrow yano said 
arbitrage is a technique of trading in two markets for example 
spot and futures simultaneously to profit from price differentials 
between them 
computeraided arbitrage selling has been blamed for recent 
market plunges although foreign brokers have denied that the 
technique has had a significant effect on the market the tokyo 
stock exchange requested shortly after the nikkeis 156910point 
fall feb 26 that securities firms limit their arbitrage deals to 
the opening minutes of the morning and the afternoon sessions until 
thursday 
</TEXT>
