<TEXT>
main events since najib replaced 
babrak karmal as president of afghanistan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1986 
may radio kabul announces that najib former head of the 
secret police is replacing president babrak karmal who was 
demoted to revolutionary council head 
december najib meets mikhail s gorbachev in moscow and 
announces a national unity government will be formed to include 
afghans living in exile 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1987 
january najib offers rebel fighters a ceasefire and expands 
his national reconciliation program to include rebel groups rebels 
reject the ceasefire as a trap they also reject najibs national 
reconciliation plan promising to fight until he is toppled and an 
islamic government is established in kabul 
april najib claims to have established national reconciliation 
commissions in 1681 villages representing about 6 percent of the 
villages in afghanistan 
september talks in geneva aimed at finding a political end to 
soviet intervention in afghanistan adjourn without agreement 
november najib proposes a 12month timetable for the 
withdrawal of soviet troops from afghanistan saying moscow has 
given it approval 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1988 
january afghan and soviet troops break a fiveweek rebel siege 
of the eastern afghan garrison town of khost najib said the 
victory was proof of his troops strength 
february gorbachev offers to withdraw his troops beginning may 
15 najib says hes confident of surviving without direct soviet 
military help 
march president reagan promises the us commitment to 
anticommunist rebels wont end with the withdrawal of soviet 
troops 
april 14 the foreign ministers of pakistan and afghanistan 
sign a united nationsbrokered accord providing for the withdrawal 
of about 103000 soviet combat troops from afghanistan within 10 
months 
may 14 several thousand soviet soldiers leave afghanistans 
second largest city kandahar and return to the soviet union 
marking the start of the negotiated troop withdrawal 
december najib convenes a grand council and proclaims himself 
president 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1989 
january several western nations including the united states 
close their embassies in kabul najib says the closures are an 
attempt to undermine his governments ability to withstand a rebel 
onslaught following the final withdrawal of soviet soldiers 
feb 15 the last soviet soldier crosses the friendship bridge 
linking afghanistan and the soviet union ending nine years of 
direct military intervention by moscow 
februarymarch najibs troops defend afghanistans eastern 
city of jalalabad against a rebel offensive his success defies 
earlier predictions that his government would crumble after the 
soviet troop withdrawal 
april 27 najib stages a revolution day parade a day early 
after learning that a faction of the army planned to kill him 
may 2021 najib convenes another council to extend a state of 
emergency imposed following the final soviet troop withdrawal 
july housetohouse searches and arrests are made after najib 
reportedly uncovers a coup plot defense minister shah nawaz tanai 
is rumored to be linked to the plot but nothing is proved and he 
holds on to his portfolio 
june an afghan army general in charge of najibs security 
defects to the guerrillas 
december searches end in 127 arrests for allegedly plotting a 
coup against najib the second such plot to be uncovered in less 
than one year maj gen tanai again is implicated and reportedly 
placed under house arrest for several weeks he is later seen in 
public with najib 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1990 
tuesday radio kabul reports tanai and mutinous soldiers tried 
to overthrow the government with the help of fighters linked to 
fundamentalist guerrilla leader gulbuddin hekmatyar the official 
radio says the coup is crushed but heavy fighting is reported 
today diplomats and moslem guerrillas report continued 
fighting in kabul with tanais forces reportedly bombing loyalist 
positions and in control of the main airport 
