<TEXT>
japans nec corp and american telephone amp 
telegraph co today announced an agreement to cooperate in 
developing and manufacturing a wide range of semiconductors and 
other technologies 
the agreement will greatly enhance the us corporations access 
to japans worlddominating electronics market 
nec the worlds largest maker of semiconductors agreed to 
cooperate with atampts microelectronics division on various projects 
for at leat five years 
under the agreement atampt microelectronics will receive a 
license to market design and produce nec gatearray computer 
chips which can be used for a wide variety of applications because 
they are programmable 
an important feature of this agreement is that customers of 
both companies will enjoy the advantage of having two stable 
sources of identical gatearray products said william warwick 
president of atampt microelectronics 
from atampt nec will receive our most sophisticated 
computeraided design tools warwick told a news conference 
he said the two companies are working on accelerating the 
placement of atampt microelectronics semiconductor products into a 
variety of nec products such as communications systems and 
computers 
atampt microelectronics which is based in berkeley heights nj 
also will provide manufacturing support for certain nec microchips 
that are widely used in consumer electronics products 
this will allow japanese customers to obtain products made by 
an american firm and will give atampt a greater presence in the 
japanese market especially with consumer electronics companies 
warwick said 
the agreement will benefit customers of both companies through 
the strength of product lines and capabilities and enhancing of 
business opportunities he said 
tomohir matsumura nec executive vice president and director of 
its semiconductor division said computer chips are often referred 
to in japan as the staple food or crude oil of the 
electronics industry 
this agreement shows that one single company cannot stand 
alone and needs more resources to survive matsumura said 
it makes sense for atampt as a big semiconductor user to go to 
nec a big semiconductor producer said charles elliott an 
electronics analyst with the investment firm goldman sachs but 
atampt is also a big semiconductor developer and it makes sense for 
atampt to design and nec to produce 
neither of the executives would attach monetary figures to the 
accord but warwick said he was confident it would be continued 
after five years 
its long enough to indicate to our customers that our access 
to gatearray technology is not a onegeneration access warwick 
said i have no doubts it will grow and continue indefinitely 
the agreement will facilitate necs policy of increasing 
purchases of foreign semiconductors to ease trade friction 
us officials angered by what they claim is a closed japanese 
market to foreign semiconductors say japan agreed to boost the 
foreign share of the semiconductor market here to 20 percent by 
july 1991 
but foreign chips share stood at only 129 percent in the final 
quarter of 1989 according to the ministry of international trade 
and industry 
nec expects to purchase 53 million worth of atampt 
semiconductors in 1990 and more in 1991 though there is no target 
figure for next year nec spokeswoman akiko sato said 
the manufacturer plans to raise its internal use of foreign 
computer chips from the current 20 percent to 23 percent by july 
1991 when the usjapan semiconductor accord expires and to some 
24 percent by the end of next year miss sato said 
the necatampt accord reflects an increasing trend toward 
corporate tieups in the semiconductor industry 
atampt microelectronics announced two weeks ago that it will 
produce semiconductor memory chips for the international market in 
a joint venture with mitsubishi electric corp another major 
japanese chip manufacturer 
international business machines corp said in january that it 
would set up a joint venture with siemens ag of west germany to 
develop advanced memory chips 
