march 4 
the reporter fond du lac wis on credit card frauds 
the story out of milwaukee the other day about credit fraud via 
card numbers retrieved from merchants trash holds a message for 
users of credit at both ends of the system 
the milwaukee gang and others around the country pulled 
carbons from merchants trash containers not only for credit 
cards but longdistance access codes and accounts with shipping 
companies as well they used the numbers for purchases and the card 
owners got the bills 
consumers tend to treat credit cards casually in truth they 
represent a great deal of money even though laws protect consumers 
from heavy losses when card numbers are used by thieves there 
still is a potential for some loss unless safeguards are taken 
the simplest is to not leave behind the carbon copy of a credit 
transaction some carbons are automatically split but even that is 
not totally safe 
credit customers should be sure to retrieve their own carbons 
after credit purchases and store clerks should be instructed to 
offer to return the carbon 
</TEXT>
