march 1 
the registerguard eugene ore on smoking 
there is good news and bad news on the smoking front 
the good news is that smoking has been banned on all 
domestic airline flights of less than six hours that means 
smokefree airplanes on all flights within the contiguous 48 states 
and on 998 percent of all domestic flights the only exceptions 
are flights of six hours or longer to alaska or hawaii 
in time given the steady march toward more smokefree 
environments it can be hoped that all domestic flights will be 
smokeless 
there is also good news in the fact that the percentage of 
american adults who smoke fell to 29 percent in 1987 from 40 
percent in 1965 
the bad news is that smoking costs the nation 52 billion a year 
in health costs and lost productivity 
thats 12 billion more than the cigarette companies generate in 
sales each year thats 390000 americans dying from 
smokingrelated causes each year more than the yearly deaths from 
all american homicides suicides auto accidents 
cocaineheroinalcohol abuse and fires combined 
</TEXT>
