<TEXT>
president bushs cabinet has evolved into the 
most powerful in a quarter century even though it meets 
infrequently insiders and analysts suggest 
when it does convene two things distinquish it from cabinet 
sessions under former president reagan the vice president speaks 
out and theres no mistaking whos the secretary of housing and 
urban development 
the full bush cabinet gets together only about once a month but 
in some months it hasnt met at all the meetings seldom last more 
than an hour and usually are held in response to some event or trip 
for instance bush called his cabinet together monday to report 
on his california summit with japanese prime minister toshiki kaifu 
and to discuss the recent nicaraguan election 
but bushs 14member cabinet may wield more power and have more 
influence with the president than any since president eisenhowers 
in the 1950s at the same time bushs white house staff is one of 
the least powerful of recent presidencies analysts suggest and 
some top bush aides agree 
while eisenhower met with his cabinet almost once a week bush 
met with his full cabinet only 11 times last year and three times 
so far this year 
one reason he gathers his cabinet so infrequently is that he 
knows the members so well some of them treasury secretary james 
a baker iii commerce secretary robert a mosbacher and treasury 
secretary nicholas f brady are among his oldest friends 
he doesnt use the full cabinet as a decisionmaking body 
said david q bates who as cabinet secretary schedules sessions 
prepares the agenda and keeps the president informed of agency 
developments 
bush constantly telephones cabinet secretaries and bates said 
he often meets individually with them such as a lunch he had 
wednesday with mosbacher reducing the need for more frequent 
fullcabinet meetings 
the secretaries can call matters to the presidents attention by 
slipping a note into bates weekly report to bush on what each 
cabinet agency is doing 
roger porter bushs domestic policy adviser who also worked in 
the reagan white house said that reagan who once failed to 
recognize his own reticient housing secretary samuel pierce at a 
gathering of mayors also held infrequent cabinet meetings 
particularly near the end of his term 
the frequency of cabinet meetings tends to deteriorate over 
time porter said 
theres little chance bush would fail to recognize his housing 
secretary jack kemp according to white house aides kemp is one 
of the most forceful and frequent speakers at cabinet sessions 
often dominating the conversations 
in fact several white house aides suggested privately that the 
irrepressible kemps outspokenness may be one reason bush doesnt 
convene the full cabinet more often kemp does not fit into the 
oldfriend category 
does kemp talk too much at cabinet meetings not at all 
said kemp spokesman robert nipp but he does talk 
another major difference between the bush and reagan cabinets 
white house aides say vice president dan quayle frequently speaks 
up 
during reagan cabinet meetings vice president bush seldom did 
bush has retained a cabinet structure set up in the reagan 
presidency in which two subcabinet groups the domestic policy 
council and the economic policy council meet frequently on major 
policy issues 
the economic group includes the secretaries of treasury 
commerce agriculture labor transportation state and the trade 
representative the domestic group includes the attorney general 
and secretaries of interior energy health and human services 
education veterans affairs and housing and urban development 
budget director richard darman sits on both councils kemp 
doesnt but usually shows up at both anyway 
those councils augmented by the national security council are 
where the bulk of the administrations top policy decisions are 
forged not within the white house staff bush frequently drops in 
on the council sessions 
with the exception of chief of staff john sununu and darman few 
on the white house staff wield much real power senior white house 
officials say privately 
stuart eizenstat a washington lawyer who was president carters 
domestic policy adviser said bushs cabinet is stronger relative 
to the white house staff than any recent cabinet 
bush broke the mold by putting his closest friends in the 
cabinet instead of on the white house staff eizenstat said 
reagan brought a whole retinue of california cronies to the 
white house and carter gave many of his georgia friends top white 
house positions by contrast few on bushs white house staff have 
known or worked with him for more than several years 
eizenstat said carters cabinet met about once a week at the 
start and then about once every two weeks but he said carter 
didnt rely much on the sessions for making decisions 
cabinet meetings are not terribly illuminating sessions you 
dont want to have your secretary of agriculture voting on whether 
to have an mx or midgetman missile system eizenstat said 
