obstacle to democratic change and want them to be replaced by 
taiwanelected politicians but chiang has praised their refusal to 
step down 
as local industrialists press for direct trade with china 
chiang claims chinese communists are trying to destabilize taiwan 
through growing trade 
chiang wego was born in shanghai on oct 6 1916 some reports 
claim that he was the adopted son of chiang kaishek and that his 
real father was tai chitao the generalissimos close friend 
i dontt really know which is my father but i am happy to be 
the son of either of them he once said 
chiang likes to socialize swap jokes and sing popular songs at 
public gatherings he has practiced chinese boxing since he was a 
child and learned to fly helicopter at age 70 
educated in prestigious military academies in germany and the 
united states chiang joined the nationalist chinese army as 
lieutenant at 25 
he was assigned to several administrative positions and served 
as lieutenant general for 14 years until being promoted to full 
general in 1985 one year before retiring he is secretary general 
of the national security council widely viewed as a symbolic seat 
with little power 
many believe chiang kaishek prevented his sons career from 
advancing quicker to avoid criticism of nepotism others believe 
that chiang wego just was not qualified to tackle key postings 
he is a nice man to make friends with but not the type of 
person who fits the post of vice presidency said chang 
chungtung a history professor at national taiwan university 
noting the trend toward democratic reform since martial law was 
lifted in 1987 after 38 years chang believes the days of the 
chiang dynasty are over and that the taiwanese people would never 
accept another family member to rule 
