if both groups agree new rates take effect if not the 
governors can ask the commission to reconsider accept the 
commission plan or overrule it but to overule they must vote 
unanimously 
mustering a unanimous vote is a difficult task most times and 
would be even less likely this year considering that the governors 
voted only 64 to submit this years proposed increase in the first 
place 
