the hostages from a humanitarian angle but by monitoring american 
moves here and there and through planting elements in regional 
american stations and after trailing some spies we have acquired 
accurate information that an american military operation is 
imminent against areas where the americans believe hostages are 
held we call upon all to watch out against this threat and beware 
and be on the alert against what america is hatching 
we are sorry over some irresponsible declarations by local 
friends in this regard that may have resulted from failing to 
understand the nature of the american movements and we call upon 
them to concentrate their humanitarian attempts on areas that can 
be more positive and more productive 
second the revolutionary justice organization holds spies and 
humanitarianism requires just punishment not a reward we warn 
america away from what it calls the hard option because we are are 
on alert we are today stronger and better prepared and more 
determined to hit out at strategic interests and deal painful 
blows washington realizes more than anyone else that our strength 
today is not that of yesterday 
third we tenaciously hold to keeping americas nose in the mud 
under our feet there is no intention to release hostages no one 
should ask for resolving the hostage issue except within the 
balanced and positive framework for which we have often proposed 
several adequate outlets on many occasions that will guarantee 
the rights of all 
victory for the oppressed in the march toward liberation and 
justice 
glory and immortality for the revered martyrs 
the revoltuionary justice organization 
