<TEXT>
a buildup of methane gas emerged 
wednesday as the suspected cause of an explosion that leveled a 
bank killing three employees and injuring 14 other people 
authorities said 
preliminary autopsy results released earlier wednesday 
discounted a bomb as the cause of the explosion tuesday at the 
crested butte state bank in this rocky mountain ski resort town 
seven people remained hospitalized in grand junction and 
gunnison three in serious condition 
montrose pathologist dr mike benzinger said he discounted a 
bomb as a cause after examining preliminary results of autopsies on 
the three dead women 
there were no marks on the victims bodies to indicate 
explosives were involved benzinger said 
the blast which occurred as the bank was opening for business 
leveled the twostory brick building reducing everything except 
the vault to rubble 
the victims were identified as donna smith 33 jade woelk and 
monica henning all of crested butte the ages of the other victims 
were not available 
state and local investigators would not speculate further on the 
cause of the explosion until federal investigators began examining 
the site 
us bureau of alcohol tobacco and firearms personnel began 
arriving wednesday 
methane as the cause is my most fervent hope said hank 
smith police chief in mount crested butte well wait for 
confirmation from atf and then well call the mine inspectors 
methane is odorless and colorless detectable only by handheld 
instruments said bill denning an inspector with the us mine 
safety and health administration in denver 
denning said it was possible that coal beds beneath or around 
the town might be producing methane as could an abandoned and 
sealed mine in the vicinity 
methane also is found in landfills because it is the product of 
decomposing organic material denning said 
a spark is needed to ignite methane said denning and there 
would be an abundance of potential spark sources in the bank 
sometimes all it takes is a light switch he said 
workers on wednesday opened a temporary bank next door to the 
explosion site the staff included an injured executive vice 
president and a retired bank employee 
the rest of the town tried to resume normal business operations 
its hard to watch people on vacation when youre in a 
tragedy said hope ostheimer a clerk in an office supply store 
its hard to hear them complain about not getting their checks 
cashed some are real sensitive but others arent and then there 
are the ones who dug through the rubble with all the rest of us 
yesterday trying to find our friends 
i guess im just angry you feel so enraged because you dont 
know what happened yet you just know theyre dead and hurt she 
said 
