state child welfare agencies are struggling to 
meet the needs of a growing number of babies born to crackaddicted 
women the department of health and human services said wednesday 
many experts said that providing protective services social 
services or foster care for such children is more complex than for 
other child welfare cases because there is more abandonment and 
violence 
case workers can spend days tracking mothers who give false 
addresses to hospitals and then abandon their babies the report 
by the inspector general said 
in some cities caseworkers are so overwhelmed that hospitals 
are stepping in with their own efforts to recruit foster parents 
the report said 
child welfare administrators and caseworkers hospital social 
services staff foster parents and state and local officials in 12 
cities were interviewed 
only eight of the cities were able to provide the number of 
crack babies reported to the child welfare system these eight 
handled 8974 such children during the previous year 
the report estimated that hospital delivery medical care and 
foster care for these babies through age 5 would be about 500 
million 
the inspector general said the estimates for the eight cities 
along with adjustments for underreporting of crack babies are 
consistent with the presidents national drug control strategy 
report estimate that 100000 babies are born to cocaineusing women 
each year 
prenatal exposure to cocaine can lead to premature birth low 
birthweight birth defects and respiratory and neurological 
problems the report said some experts say that when these 
children are older many will have severe learning disabilities and 
will need special education 
caseloads for child welfare workers in the 12 cities studied 
averaged 49 children for foster care and 161 for protective 
services the report said 
from 50 percent to 95 percent of the crack babies in the cities 
studied went home with their mother or a relative the rest go into 
foster care or some other placement arrangement 
the cities studied were chicago fort wayne ind los angeles 
miami new york newark oakland calif philadelphia phoenix 
san francisco tacoma and washington dc 
