hampshire is in presidential primaries berkowitz said at a news 
conference to announce the referendum results 
of the 141 towns that held meetings monday and tuesday 107 
voted to press the federal government to redirect surplus defense 
money to such programs as education environmental protection 
housing and health care he said 
ten towns shot down the referendum and 11 more towns postponed 
it indefinitely berkowitz said 
