<TEXT>
parched for perrier the us importer of the 
sparkling water that became a status symbol in the 1980s and the 
object of a worldwide contamination recall to start the 1990s says 
relief is a month or more away 
newly bottled perrier bearing a special marking is being shipped 
for the first time since last months recall source perrier sa 
officials said tuesday 
meantime perrier group of america plans to launch a 25 million 
marketing campaign starting today with advertisements in 22 
newspapers in an effort to keep the brands name before the public 
during shipment and to rebuild sales of what had been the 
topselling imported bottled water once it arrives 
the new bottles are expected to reach shelves in the eastern 
united states early next month and the rest of the country within 
three months 
they will carry the mark nouvelle production on the label to 
distinguish them from the 160 million bottles pulled off the market 
last month 
source perrier said tuesday in paris that shipments to 
distributors resume today but perrier group officials said it will 
take until early april for the bottles to travel overseas pass 
through customs and be distributed to the more than 1 million us 
outlets from supermarkets to bars where perrier is sold 
perrier worth waiting for is the theme of ads slated to 
appear today in usa today the wall street journal and 20 major 
market newspapers 
perrier also plans a series of humorous radio ads in the 15 
largest us markets featuring actors posing as newscasters for 
the perrier news network reporting on perrier sightings 
in one ad fictional correspondent jill purity interviews a man 
who had spotted a bottle of perrier jill notes the bottle is 
missing and the man explains that elvis presley came and drank it 
ronald v davis president and chief executive of greenwich 
connbased perrier group told reporters at the french consulate 
that humor was appropriate because no one was hurt and no 
health risk was posed by the contamination incident 
perrier was recalled feb 9 in the united states after traces of 
benzene a cancercausing chemical were found in some perrier 
bottles the recall was broadened five days later to all 160 
million bottles in 120 countries when contaminated bottles showed 
up in several other countries 
company officials claim the benzene a naturally occurring gas 
that dissolves in water entered perriers bottling line when 
workers failed to replace a filter used to screen impurities from 
the carbon dioxide gas that is mixed with the water to provide more 
fizz 
they said new quality control procedures have been installed at 
the plant in vergeze including double filtration of the gas and 
more careful monitoring 
perrier should start appearing on shelves in new york in early 
april davis said and across the country within three months he 
said it may take until the end of the summer to get all perrier 
varieties back in full distribution 
