compared to the multibilliondollar government bailout of the 
savings and loan industry 
downey told the finance subcommittee of the senate banking 
housing and urban affairs committee that when drexel no longer 
could stand on its own it collapsed the government did not rush 
in to save it nor should it have 
drexels parent company drexel burnham lambert group inc 
filed for bankruptcy code protection from creditors last month 
after defaulting on 100 million in shortterm loans and failing to 
secure additional financing 
drexel group listed more than 2000 creditors and nearly 3 
billion in liabilities 
drexels fall marked the largest securities industry bankruptcy 
filing ever and one of the first exceptions to a longheld but 
unwritten regulatory policy that some institutions are just to big 
to be allowed to fail 
downey a partner in the investment banking firm goldman sachs 
amp co put in a plug for a plan still being developed by the sia 
to allow commercial banking organizations to enter the securities 
industry and securities firms to enter consumer banking 
he said the plan would stand without forcing the deposit 
insurance system to shoulder the securities risks and without 
triggering toobigtofail status that led to the saving and 
loan bailout 
downey was among a panel of securities industry leaders 
testifying about the health and future of their industry in the 
wake of drexels demise the collapse of the junk bond market and a 
stock market plunge last october 
the panelists included john h gutfreund chairman of salomon 
inc philip j purcell chairman of dean witter financial services 
group and w lucas simons jr managing partner of jc bradford amp 
co of nashville tenn 
all four called for a single federal agency to regulate all 
aspects of the securities industry rather than the current division 
of power now among the federal reserve board securities and 
exchange commission and commodity futures trading commission 
while gutfreund wasnt specific the others said the sec should 
take up the superregulator role 
the sec should then regulate both equity and stock index 
futures markets with a recommendation that its first order of 
business be devoted to rationalizing margin requirements said 
simons of jc bradford an investment banking partnership 
concentrating on the southeast 
margins the amount of money investors must put down to buy 
securities or futures contracts on credit are much lower in the 
futures industry than in stocks critics say that encourages 
speculation in stock options through index arbitrage leading to 
sharp ups and downs in stock prices 
