the alfayed brothers who waged a bitter 1 
billion battle for harrods in 1985 exaggerated their wealth and 
background to win the famous department store a government report 
said wednesday 
mohamed ali and salah alfayed were thought to have come from a 
wealthy and established egyptian trading family that exported 
cotton to lancashire in the 19th century and built up a shipping 
empire when really they were the sons of a teacher from a poor 
quarter of alexandria egypt the report said 
the alfayeds denied wednesday that they misled anyone in 
connection with the battle for harrods owner house of fraser plc 
lonrho plc which lost the fight for harrods and has continued 
to battle the alfayeds for the past five years launched a fresh 
multipronged assault wednesday 
