as americans get ready for spring and summertime road trips last 
year the sales pace during those two months lagged mainly because 
of the attraction of incentives offered earlier in the year 
this year things could be different 
automakers and dealers are ready to let their inventories of 
unsold cars creep up in anticipation of an increased buying pace 
chrysler recently extended an incentive program through march 
for all of its vehicles except minivans and ford and gm cashback 
and lowinterest financing offers run into april or may 
what would we do if we didnt have that phillippi wondered 
about incentiveenhanced sales its pretty clear that we are 
going to have that all the way through the 1990 model year 
i cant see incentives coming down appreciably unless theres 
a heck of a lot more strength in the economy 
